observations.recommendation:
We recommended that management:

Regularly reconcile the cashbook balances with the subsidiary ledgers to ensure accuracy of the cash accounts;

Prepare and timely submit bank reconciliation statements for all accounts maintained by the Municipality;

Direct the personnel concerned to thoroughly check the recording of disbursement transactions for accuracy; and

Direct the Municipal Accountant to analyze the Trust Fund bank account with a negative balance and determine and effect the necessary adjusting and/or correcting entries to arrive at the correct balance of the account.

We recommended that management:

Adequately plan and thoroughly study each project before proposing it to be included as one of the projects to be funded by the 20% LGDF;

Enforce stringent control procedures in the disbursement of the fund to ensure that it is utilized only for its intended purpose/s to preclude the issuance of audit suspensions/disallowances;

Strictly adhere to the pertinent provisions of law, rules, and regulations relative to the utilization of the 20% Development Fund, so that constituents could directly enjoy the benefits for which the fund was primarily established;

Submit an explanation on the recurrence of such deficiency for us to decide whether to suspend/disallow said transactions in the audit.

