We recommended that management:

Enforce the immediate liquidation and/or settlement of all outstanding cash advances;

Stop the practice of granting additional cash advances to officials/employees who have previous unliquidated cash advances as well as granting multiple cash advances to the same employees regardless of the purpose;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to expedite the request for the write-off of long outstanding cash advances that are considered dormant in accordance with the guidelines and procedures provided in COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016; and

Strictly adhere to the guidelines set forth in COA Circular No. 97-002 dated February 10, 1997, in the granting and liquidation of cash advances.

We recommended for the Municipal Mayor to:

Direct the HRMO to create an employee manual that will define the job description, rights, and responsibilities, among others, of all the employees within the Municipality;

Issue a uniform and clear-cut policy on the hiring of Job Order workers to strengthen internal controls pertaining thereto;

Reduce/limit the hiring of job order workers and fill-up vacant positions; and

Evaluate and determine the appropriate personnel complement of each office.

We recommended the following:

Stop immediately the present system in handling PCF and ensure compliance with the NGAS for LGUs in maintaining the same under the imprest system;

Direct the Municipal Accountant/PCF Custodian to ensure that all disbursements under the PCV should be supported with complete supporting documents to avoid suspension and disallowance in audit;

The management should implement policies and control procedures in the granting and liquidation of cash advances through the following:

 Stop the granting of cash advance to official or employee unless the previous cash advance given to him/her is first settled or a proper accounting thereof is made in compliance with the above-referred provisions of PD1445;

Regularly send confirmation/demand letters as basis in the reconciliation of accounting and accountable officers record and as basis in imposing disciplinary measures;

Strictly comply with COA Circular No. 2012-004 for long outstanding accounts.

In compliance with COA Circular 2012-004, furnish this Audit Team with the list of accountable officers with unliquidated and outstanding cash advances, together with copy of written notices duly acknowledged by the concerned accountable officers.  Submit also copies of disbursement vouchers (DVs) and related support documents of those with outstanding balances, especially long overdue accounts.

